# KrakenHashes frontend (Vite)
#
# The app talks to the backend over RELATIVE URLs (e.g. /api/...). In the
# container nginx proxies /api to the backend, so no build-time API URL is
# needed. For a standalone `npm run dev`, Vite proxies /api (REST + the
# notifications WebSocket) to the backend — see `server.proxy` in vite.config.ts
# (default target https://localhost:31337). Change it there if your backend runs
# elsewhere.
#
# Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to client code (Vite
# convention). Add them here if you introduce build-time config, e.g.:
# VITE_EXAMPLE=value
